content:
Yes, you can absolutely change the file name manually. Here's how to do it:

1. First, check what the main.py file is importing:
```bash
# Check what main.py is importing - copy entire box
cat palios-taey-app/main.py
```

2. Then rename or copy the file based on what you find:
```bash
# If you want to rename the file - copy entire box
mv palios-taey-app/src/palios_taey/memory/service.py palios-taey-app/memory_system.py
```

Or if you prefer to keep the original and make a copy:
```bash
# If you want to make a copy - copy entire box
cp palios-taey-app/src/palios_taey/memory/service.py palios-taey-app/memory_system.py
```

This direct approach is often the simplest solution. After making this change, you can run the deployment script again.
